in_2532207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104swq1665702895834.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swq1665702895834.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swq1665702895834.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"swq1665702895834\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SSPs and Transaction Control\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, DBMS transaction control is not affected by the execution of a stored procedure. However, if transaction control is manipulated within a stored procedure, Uniface cannot guarantee a correct transaction state.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swq1665702895834__p_d36302e1_d36303e1_d36304e1\">You can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> Proc statements for DBMS transaction control.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swq1665702895834__p_d36305e1_d36306e1_d36307e1\">Multiple (parallel) transactions are supported. A stored procedure either runs in the same transaction as the calling Uniface component, or in the main transaction when called directly from a non-Uniface component.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swq1665702895834__p_d36308e1_d36309e1_d36310e1\">When the accessed entity is a Uniface Server, stored procedures are executed on the Uniface Server. This is because it must belong to the same transaction as the entity on the Uniface component.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swq1665702895834__p_d36311e1_d36312e1_d36313e1\">Global transactions (available via middleware modules ) are not supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swq1665702895834__p_d36314e1_d36315e1_d36316e1\">There is no support for NLS.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SSPs and Transaction Control Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SSPs and Transaction Control By default, DBMS transaction control is not affected by the execution of a stored procedure. However, if transaction control is manipulated within a stored procedure, Uniface cannot guarantee a correct transaction state. You can use the commit and rollback Proc statements for DBMS transaction control. Multiple (parallel) transactions are supported. A stored procedure either runs in the same transaction as the calling Uniface component, or in the main transaction when called directly from a non-Uniface component. When the accessed entity is a Uniface Server, stored procedures are executed on the Uniface Server. This is because it must belong to the same transaction as the entity on the Uniface component. Global transactions (available via middleware modules ) are not supported. There is no support for NLS. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}